A new feature that allows us to add a link to local files.

Below is the requirement :
{code}
I want to make a link to PowerPoint file on my local server in Jira. For example: in the description of a new task I want to make a hyperlink to a PowerPoint or word file on my local server so that the assignee can get the information from the linked file only by clicking the hyperlink to open the file.
We are not allowed to upload any files on the cloud due to intern rules!
{code}

{panel:title=Atlassian Update - 15 October 2020|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#2684ff|titleBGColor=#2684ff|bgColor=#ffffff}
Hi everyone, thank you for your interest in this ticket. We are currently working on bringing "actions" (checkboxes) to the editor in the new issue view. We will keep you updated on this ticket as we progress.
{panel}

Support the ability to create task lists using markdown ([https://www.markdownguide.org/extended-syntax/#task-lists]) in the new issue view.

[https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftwarecloud/markdown-formatting-in-jira-cloud-973480071.html]

h3. Issue Summary

When trying to create issues using the issue collector and the Account field is required in the project an error happens.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a new issue collector with any type – in this example, we used Customer Feedback;
 # Add the following in the field collector:
{code:java}
window.ATL_JQ_PAGE_PROPS =  {
	"triggerFunction": function(showCollectorDialog) {
		//Requires that jQuery is available! 
		jQuery("#jira-feedback-collector").click(function(e) {
			e.preventDefault();
			showCollectorDialog();
    });
  },
  fieldValues: {
    'summary': 'Test',
    //'component': '10903',
    'customfield_10058': '2'
 }
};{code}
*{{{color:#FF0000}Note that the customfield_10058 is the Account field, which is receiving the default value for the project{color}}}*

 # Submit the form.

h3. Expected Results

The issue will be successfully created.
h3. Actual Results

The issue creation fails and the following message in the network tab is displayed:
{code:html}
<html><body><textarea>{"errorMessages":[],"errors":{"customfield_10058":"Account is required."}}</textarea></body></html>{code}
h3. Workaround

Currently, there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
